org.openmuc.iec62056.data

Class DataMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openmuc.iec62056.data.DataMessage

  • public class DataMessage
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the data sent by the meter. The data consists of the manufacturer ID, the meter ID (optional), the enhanced ID/capability (optional), and a list of data sets.

      • readModeABC

        public static DataMessage readModeABC(java.io.DataInputStream is,
                                      IdentificationMessage id)
                               throws java.io.IOException
        Reads a data set, consisting of the manufacturer ID, the meter ID (optional), the enhanced ID/capability (optional), and a list of data sets, for Mode A,B and C

        Programming format: 'SOH'(0x01) Address 'STX'(0x02) 'Data block' 'ETX'(0x03) 'BCC' General format: 'STX'(0x02) 'Data block' '!' '\r'(0x0D) '\n'(0x0A) 'ETX'(0x03) 'BCC' Data block: Data sets, separated by CR and LF, Optionally the data block ends with a CR and LF Data set: Address '(' Value(optional) ('*' unit)(optional) ')'

        Parameters:
        is - The steam to read the message from
        id - The information about manufacturer ID, the meter ID (optional), the enhanced ID/capability (optional)
        Returns:
        The read data message.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if any kind of IO error occurs

        Reads a data set, consisting of the manufacturer ID, the meter ID (optional), the enhanced ID/capability (optional), and a list of data sets, for Mode D

        General format: '\r' '\n' 'Data set' '!' '\r' '\n'

        Parameters:
        is - The steam to read the message from
        id - The information about manufacturer ID, the meter ID (optional), the enhanced ID/capability (optional)
        serialPort - The serial port, used to alternate the internal timeout
        Returns:
        The read data message.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if any kind of IO error occurs
